The paper proposes a novel approach for human action understanding in videos using deep learning techniques. Specifically, the proposed model incorporates spatial and temporal information and uses attention mechanisms to learn important regions and segments in the video. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The evaluation of the proposed model is done on standard video action benchmarks, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
